<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Maine Man Killed in Truck Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ORONO, Maine (AP) -- A man was killed Friday when his pickup  
truck apparently smashed through a fence and landed in a tank of 
raw sewage, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	The man's body was recovered from the 400,000 gallon tank Friday  
afternoon after authorities noticed a hole in the fence and tire 
tracks leading into the wastewater treatment plant. 
</P>
<P>
	Upon searching the uncovered tank, they found a light blue Mazda  
pickup truck and a body next to it. 
</P>
<P>
	The holding tank was being drained to make sure there weren't  
any passengers in the truck. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials believe the car crashed into the tank sometime  
overnight. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
