<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> State's Trooper Chief Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) -- The head of Alabama's state police  
resigned under pressure Friday after questions were raised by The 
Associated Press about evidence showing his office had helped fix 
traffic tickets. 
</P>
<P>
	Gov. Don Siegelman announced Mike Sullivan's resignation.  
</P>
<P>
	``I don't know how long this practice has gone on in Alabama,  
but my administration will not tolerate this kind of action. It is 
wrong and it stops today,'' the governor said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	He said anyone involved would be punished, but he didn't  
elaborate on how far the ticket-fixing scheme may have stretched. 
Documents and interviews conducted by the AP showed some drivers 
may have appealed to state lawmakers for help. 
</P>
<P>
	Illegally fixing a traffic ticket or asking an official to do so  
is a misdemeanor in Alabama. No evidence that any money was 
involved has surfaced. 
</P>
<P>
	Sullivan, a 33-year veteran of the department, was out of town  
and could not be reached for comment Friday. He remained on the 
payroll but no longer as the head of the Department of Public 
Safety. 
</P>
<P>
	The AP reviewed copies of traffic tickets written by troopers  
over two years and payments of fines, and interviewed drivers who 
said their fines disappeared after they asked for help. Some of the 
documents, including correspondence with people whose fines were 
dropped, were signed with Sullivan's secretary's initials. 
</P>
<P>
	``If you know the right people you can get it done,'' said  
Virgil Roberts of Prattville, whose July 5 speeding ticket was 
dropped after he requested help. 
</P>
<P>
	Roberts wouldn't say who helped him with the ticket.  
</P>
<P>
	Allen Horn, manager of the Bay Oaks Golf Club near Mobile, said  
he had helped members of the golf club contact Sullivan for help 
with tickets. He said he knows several state officials because of 
the charity golf tournaments held at his course. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
