<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Torre To Name Game 1 Starter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Joe Torre isn't completely sure  
Roger Clemens will open the playoffs, saying he will decide 
Saturday between the five-time Cy Young Award winner and Orlando 
Hernandez. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've had these two guys up front, ``El Duque'' and Roger, for  
the most part the whole time,'' the New York Yankees manager said 
before Friday night's game at Tampa Bay. ``You just want to make 
sure you cover all aspects of it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Yankees will open their first-round series against Texas or  
Cleveland on Tuesday and play Game 2 Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	One factor under consideration is Clemens' performance with  
extra rest. He pitched Thursday and Game 1 falls on what normally 
would be his next day to start. 
</P>
<P>
	Pitching with two extra days of rest Thursday, Clemens struggled  
and lost the first game of a doubleheader at Baltimore. 
</P>
<P>
	``If for some reason it's not Game 1, he's just going to have to  
simulate (game preparation) to be ready when he does pitch,'' Torre 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	With the Yankees trailing 2 games to 1 in last year's AL  
championship series against Cleveland, Hernandez pitched for the 
first time in 15 days and beat the Indians at Jacobs Field. 
</P>
<P>
	Torre said the Yankees' roster for the opening playoff round  
won't be set until a team workout on Monday. Among the unanswered 
questions are whether Hideki Irabu will part of the Yankees' 10-man 
staff. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
