<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Washington To Play Va. Coach in Film </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ALEXANDRIA, Va. (AP) -- Denzel Washington will star in a movie  
about a 1971 high school football team that overcame racial strife 
to win the state championship. 
</P>
<P>
	``Remember the Titans,'' based on Alexandria's T.C. Williams  
High School, will be filmed in Atlanta, but residents here are 
getting a taste of Hollywood as Disney Films turns to the city to 
help recreate details like police uniforms and Virginia accents. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1971, the city's three high schools had just merged into T.C.  
Williams High. Two of the three schools were predominantly black. 
</P>
<P>
	The team was the center of racial tension after a white football  
coach was passed over for the top job in favor of Herman Boone, who 
will be portrayed by Washington. 
</P>
<P>
	Though rumors abound that Washington may visit the school, his  
publicist, Alan Nierob, said this week that is unlikely. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
