<HEADLINE> Airwalk Moving HQ to Colorado </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOALSBURG, Pa. (AP) -- Airwalk International plans to move its  
corporate headquarters to the Denver, Colo., area by mid-December, 
the footwear and outdoor sports equipment company announced. 
</P>
<P>
	About half of the 100-person staff at the Boalsburg headquarters  
will make the move to Colorado, according to a company news release 
yesterday. 
</P>
<P>
	The company was acquired in July by Sunrise Capital Partners, a  
New York-based investment fund, from George Yohn of Altoona, a 
company founder. 
</P>
<P>
	At the time, Airwalk officials insisted the company would stay  
local and management would stay intact. But spokeswoman Linda 
Nielander said an internal analysis concluded that a Colorado 
address would better mesh with its youthful image. 
</P>
<P>
	Airwalk targets 8- to 24-year-olds. The company is named for a  
skateboarding term. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
