<HEADLINE> Jimmy Carter Celebrates Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AMERICUS, Ga. (AP) -- Performers including Pat Boone, country  
music star Lynn Anderson and the McGuire Sisters were invited to 
the party, along with veteran members of the press. 
</P>
<P>
	Today is Jimmy Carter's 75th birthday.  
</P>
<P>
	The former president and his wife, Rosalynn, were to be honored  
tonight during two hours of entertainment at the Rylander Theater 
in Americus, 12 miles east of the Carters' hometown of Plains. 
</P>
<P>
	ABC television analyst Sam Donaldson and White House  
correspondent Helen Thomas of United Press International were 
scheduled to speak. Both covered Carter's campaign and presidency. 
</P>
