of his activities, but not anytime soon. He plans trips to England, 
Switzerland and Norway this month to raise money for the Carter 
Center, which works to improve health and sends observers to 
monitor elections worldwide. 
</P>
<P>
	``One of the nice things about having been president is Rosalynn  
and I can choose what items on a very long menu we want to 
undertake,'' Carter said. ``If we don't want to do something, we 
just say no.'' 
  	   	
</P>
