<HEADLINE> Brind'Amour's Streak Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Philadelphia Flyers center Rod Brind'Amour  
was placed on injured reserve Friday, ending the longest 
consecutive-game streak in the NHL. 
</P>
<P>
	Brind'Amour will miss Saturday's opener against Ottawa but is  
eligible to play in the Flyers' second game, against Carolina, on 
Thursday. He said he hopes to be ready by then. 
</P>
<P>
	Brind'Amour, who has played in 484 straight regular-season  
games, suffered a hairline fracture in his left foot on Sept. 25 
during the first period of the Flyers' 4-2 exhibition loss at New 
Jersey. 
</P>
