</P>
<P>
	LAKE BUENA VISTA, Fla. (AP) -- After threatening Disney with a  
boycott over an Israel exhibit they hadn't seen, some Arab and 
Muslim groups toured the display today and decided they wanted an 
exhibit for Palestinians. The delegation was escorted through the 
Israel exhibit at Epcot, which is part of Walt Disney World's 
15-month millennium celebration. The Millennium Village, which 
opened today, covers 24 countries. Some delegates said the exhibit 
was fair but they objected to what they said is the impression that 
Jerusalem is a unified city. 

