<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-01 13:50:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pfeiffer To Lead Intershop Board </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Eckhard Pfeiffer, former chief executive  
officer of Compaq Computer Corp., is taking over as chairman of 
Intershop, which helps clients build electronic storefronts on the 
Internet. 
</P>
<P>
	Pfeiffer was ousted from Compaq last spring after disappointing  
earnings. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've spent the last five months determining my next steps,''  
he said. ``I've fielded more than 100 proposals, from joining a 
board to becoming a CEO and taking on a venture capital role.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Houston resident does not plan to work full-time with the  
company. 
</P>
<P>
	``I didn't want to lock myself into a CEO position where you  
just keep going for 16 hours a day,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Pfeiffer serves on the boards of other companies, including  
General Motors and Bell Atlantic. 
</P>
<P>
	San Francisco-based Intershop was founded seven years ago in  
Germany and lost $17.3 million on sales of $20.4 million last year. 
</P>
<P>
	``I like the challenge of growing small companies into big  
global companies,'' he said. ``I think I can bring a lot to 
Intershop in terms of industry contacts. I believe this is a truly 
outstanding company in the e-commerce space.'' 




  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
