<HEADLINE> Ind. Man Sentenced in Church Arson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- A man who admitted he helped burn down a  
rural Indiana church has been sentenced to 27 months in prison. 
</P>
<P>
	Donald A. Puckett also must serve three years of probation, pay  
a $1,500 fine and perform 450 hours of community service for his 
conviction on an arson charge, U.S. Attorney Judith A. Stewart said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Puckett, 38, admitted helping Jay Scott Ballinger and  
Ballinger's girlfriend, Angela Wood, burn the Concord Church of 
Christ in Lebanon, in January 1994. The century-old white frame 
church was featured in the opening scene of the movie ``Hoosiers.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Puckett admitted Thursday he sprayed a flammable mixture of  
gasoline, kerosene and paint thinner while Wood wrote satanic 
symbols on the porch and Ballinger lit the fire. 
</P>
<P>
	Wood, 24, also has been charged with arson.  
</P>
<P>
	Ballinger, 37, is accused of burning a total of 33 churches in  
California, Georgia, Indiana, Kentucky, Missouri, Ohio, South 
Carolina and Tennessee since 1994. He is scheduled to stand trial 
Feb. 7. 
  	   	
</P>
