<HEADLINE> Wizards Sign Power Forward Smith </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Washington Wizards, looking for better  
performance on the boards, signed free agent power forward Michael 
Smith on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	A five-year NBA veteran, Smith has averaged 6 points and 7.1  
rebounds per game with Sacramento and Vancouver. 
</P>
<P>
	Although terms of the contract weren't disclosed, the Wizards  
had a $2 million roster exemption available to cover the first year 
of Smith's contract. 
</P>
<P>
	``Michael instantly makes us a better rebounding team,'' Wizards  
general manager Wes Unseld said. ``He is a solid rebounder, has 
good defensive skills, and that's why the coaches and I feel he 
will be an asset.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-8 Smith, a Washington native, will compete with Aaron  
Williams, who played for Seattle last year, for the starter's job 
at power forward. Smith had been traded to Orlando last month as 
part of an 11-player, three-team deal. 
</P>
<P>
	The Wizards open their training camp Monday at Shepherd College  
in Shepherdstown, W.Va. 
  	   	
