<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Knicks Fill Out Camp Roster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The New York Knicks signed free agents Ivano  
Newbill and Antonio Smith to non-guaranteed contracts Friday, 
filling out their training camp roster. 
</P>
<P>
	Newbill, a three-year veteran, last played in the NBA in 1997-98  
with Vancouver. The 6-foot-9 forward has averaged 1.5 points and 
2.6 rebounds over 134 career games. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith, an undrafted rookie from Michigan State, averaged 6.7  
points and 7.9 rebounds in college. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot-8, 250-pound Smith, a forward, was acquitted Thursday  
by a jury on charges of breaking a cooler lock and stealing a 
40-ounce beer from a convenience store in East Lansing, Mich. Smith 
was accused along with a former Michigan State teammate, Mateen 
Cleaves. 
</P>
<P>
	The Knicks' roster now stands at 17. Centers Patrick Ewing and  
Chris Dudley are injured will not be available for the team's first 
practice Tuesday in Charleston, S.C. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
