<HEADLINE> Ohio State Hoops Exec Is Charged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- The director of operations for Ohio  
State's men's basketball team has been charged with domestic 
violence and disorderly conduct. 
</P>
<P>
	Delaware County Sheriff's deputies arrested Randall Shrout, 49,  
at his home near Powell on Monday night. Also charged was Shrout's 
girlfriend, Tammy Oakes, 37, who lives with Shrout. 
</P>
<P>
	Both have been charged with two counts of domestic violence and  
one count of disorderly conduct, Maj. Gil Borchers said today. 
</P>
<P>
	Shrout is accused of grabbing Oakes by the throat and  
threatening her and ransacking his home, Borchers said. Oakes is 
accused of hitting Shrout over the head with a telephone. 
</P>
<P>
	Shrout pleaded innocent to the charges. Oakes is to be arraigned  
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	A message seeking comment was left for Shrout at his office  
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Athletic director Andy Geiger said he has talked to Shrout about  
what happened, but will let the courts handle the matter before 
determining whether anything should be done. 
</P>
<P>
	Shrout's duties include coordinating team travel and overseeing  
team managers, camps and clinics. He also helps with recruiting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
