<HEADLINE> Hyde Named AP Auto Writer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Justin Hyde, a business writer for The Associated  
Press, has been appointed the AP's auto writer. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Friday by Charles Hill, chief of  
bureau for the AP in Michigan. 
</P>
<P>
	Hyde, 26, joined the AP in Kansas City in 1995 and transferred  
to Detroit the next year. He transferred to Lansing in 1997 and 
covered state government before returning to Detroit as business 
writer in 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Hyde is a native of Marshfield, Mo., and a graduate of the  
University of Missouri. 
  	   	
