<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Olczyk Re-Signs With Blackhawks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Eddie Olczyk, a Chicago-born center who returned  
to the Blackhawks last season after stops with five other teams, 
signed a contract Friday with the team. 
</P>
<P>
	Contract details weren't released.  
</P>
<P>
	Olczyk, 33, has 340 goals, 450 assists and 862 penalty minutes  
in 998 games with six NHL teams over 15 seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	A 1983-84 U.S. National Team member and third pick overall in  
the 1984 entry draft, Olczyk started his NHL career in Chicago, 
then played with Toronto, Winnipeg, the New York Rangers, Winnipeg, 
Los Angeles and Pittsburgh before returning to the Blackhawks last 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	As a rookie with Chicago in 1985, he had six goals and five  
assists in 15 playoff games. 
</P>
<P>
	He was a member of the 1994 Rangers' Stanley Cup championship  
squad. His most productive seasons were 1989 and 1990 with Toronto 
when he scored 90 and 88 points respectively. He had a career-best 
42 goals in 1988, then scored five goals in six playoff games. 
</P>
<P>
	Last season, he had 10 goals and 15 assists in 61 games.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
