<HEADLINE> Rapids 1, Clash 0, SO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- The Colorado Rapids failed to score for the third  
straight game but prevailed in a shootout for a 1-0 victory over 
the San Jose Clash on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rapids have gone 319 minutes of regulation without scoring  
and have managed just three goals over their last 11 games. The New 
York-New Jersey MetroStars hold the Major League Soccer record for 
the longest scoring drought, going 375 minutes without a goal 
earlier this season. 
</P>
<P>
	Colorado keeper Ian Feuer made three saves in regulation and  
turned away all three penalty kicks by the Clash (18-13) in the 
shootout for his eighth shutout of the season. 
</P>
<P>
	Rapids midfielder Anders Limpar returned to the lineup after  
missing 11 games with a strained left quadriceps. He scored the 
clinching penalty kick, beating San Jose keeper Joe Cannon. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rapids (20-10) missed a chance to gain ground in the Western  
Conference. Colorado is three points behind first-place Los Angeles 
with two games remaining. The Galaxy can clinch the conference 
title with a regulation victory Sunday against Dallas. 
  	   	
</P>
