<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	
</P>
<P>
 *Hewlett-Packard Co., down 3 3/16 at 87 9/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The Palo Alto, Calif.-based computer maker warned that its  
fiscal fourth-quarter revenues could fall short of Wall Street 
expectations. The company attributed the shortfall in part to 
component shortages due to the earthquake in Taiwan. 

</P>
<P>
 *Revlon Inc., down 4 5/16 at 13 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The New York-based company, one of the best-known makers of  
cosmetics and consumer products, said it is in talks to sell its 
salon-based business and some Latin American brands. Ronald O. 
Perelman, the billionaire businessman who controls Revlon, put the 
company up for sale in April, but was unable to find a buyer. 

</P>
<P>
 *Service Corp. International, down 3 at 7 9/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The Houston-based funeral and cemetery company expects its  
third-quarter earnings to fall below Wall Street analysts' 
estimates. Service attributed the shortfall to lower rates of death 
in the United States. 

</P>
<P>
 *York International Corp., down 13 15/16 at 22    	
</P>
<P>
	The York, Pa.-based company expects to report third-quarter  
earnings that are below Wall Street analysts' estimates. York, 
which makes heating, ventilation, air conditioning and 
refrigeration products, attributed some of the shortfall to weak 
economic conditions in Latin America. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	
</P>
<P>
 *Worthington Foods Inc., up 8 5/8 ay 23  
</P>
<P>
 *Kellogg Co., down 9/16 at 36 7/8 on the NYSE 
</P>
<P>
	Kellogg, the Battle Creek, Mich.-based cereal giant, agreed to  
acquire vegetarian food maker Worthington Foods for $307 in an 
effort to diversify its product line. Worthington Foods, based in 
Worthington, Ohio, markets products under the Morningstar Farms, 
Natural Touch, Worthington, and Loma Linda brands. 

</P>
<P>
 *Willis Lease Finance Corp., down 6 5/8 at 6 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The Sausalito, Calif.-based company which leases aircraft parts  
expects to report a loss in the third quarter. Willis Lease said 
lower leased equipment sales and lower sales of aircraft and engine 
parts at the company's aeronautical unit hurt third-quarter 
results. 

</P>
<P>
 *Apex Inc., down 4 11/16 at 14    	
</P>
<P>
	The Redmond, Wash.-based company, which designs switching  
systems and services for client server networks, expects its 
third-quarter earnings to fall below Wall Street analysts' 
estimates. Apex said the shortfall was due in part to losing 
Hewlett-Packard Co. as a customer. 

</P>
<P>
 *Excite atHome, up 2 7/8 at 44 5/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The Redwood City, Calif., company, which provides high-speed  
Internet access over cable lines, said it is continuously assessing 
various forms of strategic relationships. There's speculation that 
Excite atHome is in talks with America Online for a possible 
alliance or merger. 




  	   	
</P>
