<HEADLINE> Lakers Sign Forward Stephen Howard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- The Los Angeles Lakers signed 6-foot-9  
forward Stephen Howard on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Howard played with four NBA teams in four seasons since joining  
Utah as a free agent from DePaul in 1992. Howard played in Greece 
last season, averaging 17.7 points and 8.8 rebounds. His NBA 
average is 2.8 points and 1.4 rebounds per game. 
</P>
<P>
	Contract terms weren't disclosed. The Lakers have 17 players  
signed for the opening of training camp Tuesday. The first 
exhibition is Oct. 12 with the 1999-00 season beginning Nov. 2. 
</P>
<P>
	Howard's signing is the third this week in which the Lakers  
appear to be seeking frontcourt backup. Centers Benoit Benjamin, 
34, and John Salley, 35, were signed Wednesday. 
  	   	
