<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> European Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- European stocks fell Friday over fears of rising  
interest rates as central bankers in the United States and Europe 
prepare to meet next week. 
</P>
<P>
	Telecommunications shares were the worst performers, with the  
Dow Jones Stoxx Telecoms index down 2.0 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	Vodafone AirTouch, its biggest component by market value, fell  
12 pence to 275 pence, and Deutsche Telekom, the second biggest, 
fell 92 cents to 38.24 euros. 
</P>
<P>
	Meanwhile, Stoxx Ltd., the company that compiles the Dow Jones  
Stoxx family of indexes, reported Friday that the telecoms index 
was the best performer in Europe during September. 
</P>
<P>
	On Friday, the Dow Jones Stoxx Index fell 2.42 points, or 0.8%,  
to close at 301.49. 
</P>
<P>
	Pharmaceutical stocks also declined, led by Glaxo Wellcome,  
which lost 29 pence to close at 1,555 pence in London after a 
British institute said the company's Relenza flu drug shouldn't yet 
be prescribed in the National Health Service. 
</P>
<P>
	Also in London, BAA was the worst performing blue-chip share,  
shedding 17.5 percent, or 107.5 pence, to close at 507.5 pence 
after the airports and duty-free group said the end of duty free 
shopping within Europe would hurt profits by more than had been 
expected. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index, which tracks 310 companies in  
countries that joined the single currency, closed down 1.79 points 
at 316.90. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index fell 27.37 points to 3642.34,  
while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index closed down 31.52 points at 3598.09. 
</P>
<P>
	In domestic markets, London's FTSE 100 index closed down 1  
percent, Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index fell 0.5 percent, the Paris 
CAC-40 index fell 0.9 percent and Amsterdam's AEX index fell 1.6 
percent. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
