<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Five Found Dead in N. Carolina Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WAYNESVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Authorities responding to a report of a  
shooting found five people dead in a home, a sheriff's department 
official said today. 
</P>
<P>
	The victims were found late Thursday in a residence near  
Interstate 40, Haywood County Chief Deputy Jimmy Parton said. He 
said he didn't know whether they had died from gunshot wounds and 
provided no other details. 
</P>
<P>
	Dorothy Price, who lives a half-mile away from the crime scene  
north of Waynesville, said she knew the victims and they all were 
members of the same family. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a normally quiet area,'' Price said this morning. ``We've  
never had anything like this happen before.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Waynesville is about 30 miles west of Asheville, near the Great  
Smoky Mountains National Park on the North Carolina-Tennessee line. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
