<HEADLINE> Travel Magazine's Must-See List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	National Geographic Traveler's list of the places the  
well-traveled person should visit sometime in his life. 
</P>
<P>
	--Urban Spaces: Cities for the ages. Barcelona, Hong Kong,  
Istanbul, Jerusalem, London, New York, Paris, Rio de Janeiro, San 
Francisco, Venice. 
</P>
<P>
	--Wild Places: Last bastions of Eden. Amazon forest, Antarctica,  
Australian Outback, Canadian Rockies, coral reefs of Papua-New 
Guinea, Galapagos Islands, the Grand Canyon, Sahara desert, 
Serengeti plain, Venezuela's Tepuis highlands. 
</P>
<P>
	--Paradise Found: beauty, serenity and heavenly pleasures.  
Italy's Amalfi coast, Boundary Waters in Minnesota, British Virgin 
Islands, Greek islands, Hawaiian islands, Japanese Ryokan inns, 
Kerala in India, Pacific islands, Seychelles in the Indian Ocean, 
Torres del Paine National Park in Chile. 
</P>
<P>
	Country Unbound: Civilization and nature in harmony. The Alps,  
Big Sur in California, Canadian Maritime provinces, coastal Norway, 
Danang to Hue in Vietnam, England's Lake District, Loire Valley in 
France, North Island in New Zealand, Tuscany, Vermont. 
</P>
<P>
	World Wonders: Our monumental creations. Acropolis in Athens,  
Angkor, cyberspace, the Great Wall in China, Machu Picchu in Peru, 
Mesa Verde in Colorado, Petra in Jordan, the Pyramids, Taj Mahal 
and Vatican City. 
</P>
<P>
	Bonus: a destination for the future. Space.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
