<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Baseball Releases Playoff Schedule </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The New York Yankees will play their first two  
playoff games in prime time, the Atlanta Braves will start in the 
daytime and the Arizona Diamondbacks will play after much of the 
country has gone to sleep. 
</P>
<P>
	The Yankees will play Cleveland or Texas on Tuesday and  
Thursday, the commissioner's office said Friday, with the opener to 
be broadcast by NBC and the second game by Fox. Games are scheduled 
to start at around 8:07 p.m. EDT. 
</P>
<P>
	In the other first-round series, the Boston Red Sox and Pedro  
Martinez will open Wednesday at Cleveland or Texas in prime time on 
Fox at 8:07 p.m. EDT, then play the following afternoon at 4:09 
p.m. on ESPN. 
</P>
<P>
	Atlanta's first two games, most likely against Cincinnati or  
Houston, will be Tuesday and Wednesday at 4:09 p.m., both on ESPN. 
</P>
<P>
	Arizona's first two games, also likely to be against Cincinnati  
or Houston, will be Tuesday and Wednesday at 11:09 p.m. EDT. 
</P>
<P>
	Baseball used to fix the sites of all postseason games in  
advance, but decided after the 1997 season to use regular-season 
records to determine the home-field advantage. 
</P>
<P>
	Because the top teams were tightly bunched going into the final  
three days of the regular season, only Atlanta was assured of 
playing the first two games at home when the schedule was released 
early Friday evening. 
</P>
<P>
	Boston, Cleveland, the Yankees and Texas were assured of playoff  
spots in the AL, and Arizona and Atlanta had clinched in the NL. 
Cincinnati, Houston and the New York Mets were competing for the 
final two berths. 
</P>
<P>
	The NL championship series starts Oct. 12 and the AL  
championship series the following day. The World Series begins Oct. 
23 at the NL champion and Game 7 would be at the NL ballpark on 
Oct. 31 -- the latest date ever for a Series game. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
