<HEADLINE> Leafs Trade Modin to Tampa Bay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Left wing Fredrik Modin was traded by the Toronto  
Maple Leafs to the Tampa Bay Lightning on Friday for defenseman 
Cory Cross and a 2001 seventh-round draft pick. 
</P>
<P>
	Modin, 24, is beginning his fourth NHL season. The 6-foot-4  
Swede had 16 goals and 15 assists in 67 games last season, playing 
mostly with leading scorer Mats Sundin. He was dropped from the top 
line late last season, and was scoreless in eight playoff games. 
</P>
<P>
	Cross, 28, who re-signed Thursday with Tampa Bay, had two goals  
and 16 assists in 67 games last season, his sixth with the 
Lightning. Tampa Bay had the league's worst record last season. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm excited about going to a contender,'' Cross said. ``It'll  
be good to get into a progressive, winning environment.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Cross flew to Montreal to join the Leafs for their season opener  
Saturday night against the Canadiens. 
  	   	
</P>
