<HEADLINE> Judge Orders Reattachment of Penis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NORWALK, Conn. (AP) -- A man who cut off his penis in an apparent  
suicide attempt was ordered by a judge to have it reattached. 
</P>
<P>
	Wednesday's ruling came at the request of Norwalk Hospital,  
after the 42-year-old man refused the surgery for his 
self-inflicted injury. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said they received a call early Wednesday that said a man  
was running along a street holding a towel to his bleeding groin. 
Officers tracked the blood to a house and found the man inside. 
</P>
<P>
	He told authorities that someone had told him if he cut off his  
penis he would bleed to death, police said. A paramedic found the 
severed penis on the apartment floor. 
</P>
<P>
	Following the court ruling, the man was taken to Yale-New Haven  
hospital for surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	It was unclear Friday if the surgery was successful.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
